        }, this), /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("p", {
          children: "My scores were good, and I could have gone to BJB, Ravenshaw or Khalikote College for 10+2, but for some reason, I did not, and I studied in the same locality where we had a small college. I was not interested at all in medicine. I always had REC Rourkela in my mind when I thought about engineering. There was no access to coaching for me, and I had to do all the studies myself. Sometimes I regret not having gone to Bhubaneswar or Cuttack or even Berhampur, which was nearby, because I could not get better exposure and lifestyle where I was studying. I was a lot into extra-curricular \u2014 dramatics, writing scripts, acting in plays, elocutions, debate competitions, and whatnot. In college, we were competing with students from CBSE and ICSE background, and even the medium of instruction was different. The promptness of other students during interaction in classrooms made us feel inferior, and we had our complexities and insecurities. But the last 12 years of studies and our upbringing made us really tough, and we sailed through it."
