        }, this), /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("p", {
          children: "I was an employee of TRL twice and NIT Rourkela twice. I was doing very well at TRL, and it was a very fast-paced learning process there. I installed refractories in various steel plants of SAIL and other private manufacturing units of petroleum. The professional career was up-and-coming there. It was Prof. R K Sinha, who encouraged me to pursue higher studies. He was the HOD at that time and also an advisor to TRL. Being his student, we had constant interactions in the company. During one such interaction, I was asked whether I am enjoying or not. To which I replied positively that it was exciting, but any well-trained person could do it, as it became easy after a while. After introspection, I realized that I would be better off doing intellectual stuff and would be at peace with myself. I got a Junior Lecturer post in NIT Rourkela and started teaching and doing projects with Prof. S. Bhattacharya and Prof. S. K. Pratihar. After a couple of years, I went on for Ph.D. in the USA and came back to join TRL again then joined NIT Rourkela in 2011."
