        }, this), /*#__PURE__*/_jsxDEV("p", {
          children: "As a B Tech graduate, the decisions are mostly influenced by what the society perceives of you. Typically, one of them is how much money you earn is kind of a measure of how successful you are. In addition to that, core industries include physically stressful manufacturing jobs, and they are not generally attractive owing to various other factors. On the other hand, non-core jobs have a lovely setting, curated building, pleasant atmosphere, air-conditioned chambers, etc. It is easy for a 22-23-year-old person to be pulled by such prospects. Adding to it, the recent explosion in opportunities in those sectors like Al, analytics, Big Data, etc. All these factors combine to the diverting of students to the non-core industry. But then some students are intrinsically wired to it, and not only for the glamour of it."
